      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(github-copilot): bound usage response reads",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`fetchCopilotUsage` in `extensions/github-copilot/usage.ts` reads the usage response with an unbounded `await res.json()`. The shared fetch layer applies an abort timeout but does **not** bound the body, so a misbehaving or compromised endpoint can stream an arbitrarily large response that is fully buffered into memory — a memory-pressure / hang (OOM) vector on the usage path.\n\n## Evidence\n\nReuses the shared bounded reader `readProviderJsonResponse` (16 MiB cap, cancels the stream on overflow) — same pattern as the recently merged #95218 / #96027 / #96038. Plugin-scoped, no new abstraction; brings GitHub Copilot usage in line with the other providers' bounded JSON reads.\n\nReal behavior proof (live vitest, not mocked): a real `ReadableStream` streaming a body past the cap is fed through `fetchCopilotUsage`, asserting it rejects with `github-copilot-usage: JSON response exceeds ...`, the stream is canceled, and `bytesPulled < cap` (not fully buffered).\n\n```\nTests  29 passed (29)\n```\n",
